## Decisions and Action Items

* **`draft-ietf-opsawg-rfc5706bis`:** WGLC is extended. Participants are encouraged to provide final reviews on the list.
* **`draft-ietf-opsawg-pcapng`:** The chairs are actively seeking a volunteer to act as the document shepherd.
* **`draft-ietf-opsawg-yang-provenance`:** The authors decided to split the YANG canonicalization/normalization issue into a separate document to avoid stalling the core provenance draft.
* **`draft-ietf-opsawg-scheduling-oam-tests`:** An early YANG Doctor review will be initiated once the authors post their settled proposal regarding the Router/Node ID issue to the list.
* **IPFIX WG Placement:** The chairs (Joe and Benoit) will coordinate with the Area Directors (Mahesh and Warren) to determine whether technology-specific IPFIX drafts (e.g., BIER, BGP POV, BGP VPN) should be progressed in OPSAWG or transferred to their respective technology-focused working groups.

